# {{ project_name }} — Project Standards

This document captures project-specific rules the PM agent enforces
during PR review. Edit it freely — the validator reads this file and
the PM agent's review checks it. Anything you write here is something
the agent will try to enforce.

## Naming conventions

- Issue keys use the `{{ key_prefix }}-<N>` prefix.
- Concept node ids are lowercase slugs: `user-model`, `auth-token-endpoint`, `dec-003-session-tokens`.
- Session ids are descriptive slugs: `api-endpoints-core`, `critical-prod-fix`.

## Body conventions

- Every issue body must have these top-level headings (the validator checks this):
  `Context`, `Implements`, `Repo scope`, `Requirements`, `Execution constraints`,
  `Acceptance criteria`, `Test plan`, `Dependencies`, `Definition of Done`.
- Every issue must have at least one `[[concept-node]]` reference somewhere in
  the body — otherwise the validator warns about a coherence gap.
- Every issue must include the "stop and ask" guidance so agents know they
  can bail out on ambiguity instead of guessing.
- Acceptance criteria must be checkboxes (`- [ ] ...`), not prose.

## Concept graph

- Create a concept node whenever a concept is referenced by 2+ issues OR
  crosses a repo boundary. One-off mentions stay as inline prose.
- Every active node must have a valid `source` with `content_hash` set.
  The PM agent rehashes nodes during the update workflow.
- `related` on concept nodes is bi-directional. If A.related contains B,
  B.related must contain A. The validator auto-fixes this.

## Session artifacts

- Sessions in `completed` status must have all required artifacts from
  `templates/artifacts/manifest.yaml`. The validator enforces this.
- `plan.md` and `verification-checklist.md` are written during the planning
  phase. `task-checklist.md` is written as the session enters `in_progress`.
  `recommended-testing-plan.md` and `post-completion-comments.md` are
  written as the session reaches `done`.

## Commits and PRs

- Branch naming: `<agent-id>/<ISSUE-KEY>-<slug>` (e.g. `claude/{{ key_prefix }}-42-auth-endpoint`).
- Commit messages reference the issue key in the first line.
- PR title starts with `[{{ key_prefix }}-<N>] <summary>`.
- Draft a PR body from the completion comment template.

## Validation gate

- Every batch of file writes must be followed by:
  `tripwire validate`
- Fix every error. Do not commit until `exit_code` is 0.
- The gate also rebuilds the graph cache as a side effect — no need to
  run `refs rebuild` separately.
